executor_description: Get all organisations created by partner  Can be filtered by organisationName in search of a specific organisation Can do pagnitaed call with page and pageSize
Get active benefits of an organisation.
Get active members of an organisation and benefit.  Can send a memberId (optional) in params to get active data of a specific member and their dependents. (Check example #2)
Delete an non-onboarded organisation (organisation who do not have any benefit) It deletes  Organisation record All members and dependents of the organisation Estimate of the organisation
Creates an organisation in Plum.
Retrieve the organisation.  A partner can only retrieve the organisation that are created by the partner.
An endorsement can not be updated, Partners can delete any non required endorsement and create a fresh one.  Also, Endorsements in completed state can not be deleted.
Create Endorsement
If invoice grandtotal is 0 for any endorsement, then payment details are not required.
An activity can be deleted from endorsement.  Returns updated endorsement and premium (if any).
Retrieve Endorsement
List Endorsement
If invoice grandtotal is 0 for any endorsement, then payment details are not required.
New additions/modifications/deletions can be added in endorsement.
Generate a token using partnerId and secret.  Each generate token call will generate a new token and will delete the previous one.
A token can be refreshed and a new token can be obtained using this API.

In case of graded sum insurance, members can be assigned respective graded sum insured.  This will update the existing estimates against the organisation or will create a new estimate as per the update in sum insured Existing member's sum insured can be reset to null. In that case an organisation default sum insured will get applicable to that member
Retrieve a member.  Response contains all dependent of the member.
Dependents can be added for a member.  If organisation has active benefits, An estimate will be generated for member level updates.
Create members in an organisation.

In case of graded sum insurance, members can be assigned respective graded sum insured.  This will update the existing estimates against the organisation or will create a new estimate as per the update in sum insured Existing member's sum insured can be reset to null. In that case an organisation default sum insured will get applicable to that member
List Estimates
Retrieve the estimate.
We will need a payment confirmation from the partners side. It checks if the payment amount matches with estimate amount or not.
Health ID Card image can be downloaded with this API for any member or dependent.

We enable partners to provide a logged-in experience to their members using the passwordless-login API.  Member can see a login to plum on partners dashboard and this API redirects member to their plum dashboard.  We recommened partners to create an API like /goToPlum, which internally hits this API and redirects member to their plum dashboard.
